      "level": 1,
      "text": "Appendix II: Consonant Names"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "Since some consonants share the same sound, names have been invented to distinguish between such characters, just like when you say \"A is for apple\". Thai consonant names are consistent and understood throughout Thailand. If you just want to be able to read basic Thai then I suppose you don't really need to know these, but if you want to expand your vocabulary it's the only way Thais can spell words out for you."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "The order you see below is the actual alphabetical order of Thai consonants. Memorising it will help you when using a dictionary, but unless you've got time, these can be overlooked for the time being."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "html": "By the way, I also include 2 obsolete consonants ฃ and ฅ here as well. They're no longer used but still in the alphabet list."
    },
